{
  "doc_id": "32396",
  "text": "Basal insulin therapy should be considered when introducing dual or triple therapy and should be intensified adding a mealtime insulin or a GLP-1 RA when glycemic control needs to be optimized [CITATION_1] . In this sense, the combination of basal insulin and GLP-1 RA could already be indicated as first step (in states of very poor glycemic control) or as second step (from monotherapy to triple therapy).",
